My first blog post (on my personal blog that is)! To honor this occasion, here's Hello World! in all the programming languages I know and actually use somewhat frequently (else I'd have dozens more, also markup languages don't count)

AppleScript:
<pre class="theme:monokai lang:applescript decode:true ">display dialog "Hello World!"</pre> 


AutoIt:
<pre class="theme:monokai lang:autoit decode:true ">#include &lt;MsgBoxConstants.au3&gt;
 
Msgbox($MB_ICONINFORMATION, "", "Hello World!")</pre> 

Bash:
<pre class="lang:default decode:true " >echo "Hello World!"</pre> 

C:
<pre class="lang:c decode:true " >#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main(void) {
    printf("Hello World!");
}</pre> 

C++:
<pre class="lang:c++ decode:true " >#include &lt;iostream&gt;
 
int main(){
    std::cout &lt;&lt; "Hello World!\n";
}</pre> 

C++ w/Qt:
<pre class="lang:c++ decode:true " >#include &lt;QCoreApplication&gt;
#include &lt;QDebug&gt;
 
int main(int argc, char *argv[]){
    QCoreApplication a(argc, argv);
    qDebug() &lt;&lt; "Hello World!";
    return a.exec();
}</pre> 

C#:
<pre class="lang:c# decode:true " >using System;
class Program {
    public static void Main(string[] args) {
        Console.WriteLine("Hello World!");
    }
}</pre> 

Delphi:
<pre class="lang:delphi decode:true " >program HelloWorld;
begin
  Writeln('Hello World!');
end.</pre> 

Java:
<pre class="lang:java decode:true " >public class HelloWorld {
   public static void main(String[] args) {
       System.out.println("Hello World!");
   }
}</pre> 

JavaScript:
<pre class="lang:js decode:true " >console.log('Hello World!');</pre> 

Objective-C:
<pre class="lang:objc decode:true " >#import &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#import &lt;Foundation/Foundation.h&gt;
 
int main(void){
    NSLog(@"Hello World!\n");
    return 0;
}</pre> 

PHP:
<pre class="lang:php decode:true " >&lt;?php echo 'Hello World!'; ?&gt;</pre> 

Python: 
<pre class="lang:python decode:true " >print "Hello World!"</pre> 

Ruby:  
<pre class="lang:ruby decode:true " >puts "Hello World!"</pre> 

Swift:  
<pre class="lang:swift decode:true " >println("Hello World!")</pre> 

Visual Basic:  
<pre class="lang:vb decode:true " >MsgBox "Hello World!"</pre> 

VB.NET:
<pre class="lang:vbnet decode:true " >Module HelloWorld
    Sub Main()
        Console.WriteLine("Hello World!")
    End Sub
End Module</pre>
